HEADWORD: Pharmacolite
<hw>Phar*mac"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> drug, poisonous drug + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pharmacolithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A hydrous
arsenate of lime, usually occurring in silky fibers of a white or
grayish color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

